menu "Example Configuration"

config EXAMPLE_ESP_SECURE_CERT_ENABLE_CI
    bool
    default n
    help
        Enable this option to apply configuration settings required for running
        the esp_secure_cert example in Continuous Integration (CI) environments.
        This may include settings for automated testing, mock data, or other
        CI-specific behaviors. It is not intended for production use.

config EXAMPLE_ESP_SECURE_CERT_WRITE_DEMO
    bool "Enable write functionality demo"
    default n
    help
        Enable this option to run a simple write functionality demonstration.
        This shows how to use esp_secure_cert_append_tlv() to write custom
        user data to the esp_secure_cert partition.

        WARNING: This will erase and modify the esp_secure_cert partition!
        Only enable for testing or on devices without production credentials.

endmenu
